reviewText: My son's favorite Nature episode was the Island of Cuba that featured some of the native species on the tropical island paradise. Including the Crocodiles and the Iguanas.

This is a very informative DVD. We especially liked the one about Cuba, since we were amazed at the interesting fauna of this island; the Cuban crocodile leaping out of the water and the terrestrial crabs that migrate to the ocean to lay their eggs forming a larvae soup. We highly recommend it.
I did find it odd to have these two particular locations on the same video but "Nature" the program does well with both.
There's nothing not to like about this DVD, the only thing is it makes you want to be there with the birds, beautiful.
